148 8.] 4. Before July sixteenth of each year, each adult provider shall report the
149 following metrics to the department for each individual cohort, on a cohort-by-cohort basis:
150 (1) The total number of students who have been funded through the program;
151 (2) The total number of credits earned;
152 (3) The total number of employability skills certifications issued;
153 (4) The total number of industry-recognized credentials, stackable credentials, and
154 technical skills assessments earned for each tier of funding; and
155 (5) The total number of graduates[;
156 (6) The average cost per graduate once the stipulated time to make such a calculation
157 has passed; and
158 (7) The graduation rate once the stipulated time to make such a calculation has
159 passed].
160 [9.] 5. (1) Before September sixteenth of each year, each [approved] adult program
161 provider shall conduct and submit to the department the aggregate results of a survey of each
162 individual cohort, on a cohort-by-cohort basis, who graduated from the program of the
163 [approved] adult program provider under this section. The survey shall be conducted in the
164 year after the year in which the individuals graduate and the next four consecutive years.
165 (2) The survey shall include at least the following data collection elements for each
166 year the survey is conducted:

HCS HB 3239 7
167 (a) The individual's employment status, including whether the individual is employed
168 full time or part time;
169 (b) The individual's hourly wages;
170 (c) The individual's access to employer-sponsored health care; and
171 (d) The individual's postsecondary enrollment status, including whether the
172 individual has completed a postsecondary certificate or degree program.
173 [10.] 6. (1) Beginning at the end of the second fiscal year of the program, the
174 department shall review data from each [approved] adult program provider to ensure that
175 each is achieving a minimum [program performance standards including, but not limited to:
176 (a) A minimum] fifty percent average graduation rate per cohort[; and
177 (b) An average cost per graduate per cohort of seven thousand dollars or less].
178 (2) Any [approved] adult program provider that fails to meet the minimum program
179 performance standards described in subdivision (1) of this subsection shall be placed on
180 probationary status for the remainder of the fiscal year by the department.
181 (3) Any [approved] adult program provider that fails to meet the minimum program
182 performance standards described in subdivision (1) of this subsection for two consecutive
183 years shall be removed from the Missouri course access and virtual school program under
184 section 161.670 approved program provider list by the department.
185 [11.] 7. (1) No [approved] adult program provider shall discriminate against a
186 student on the basis of race, color, religion, national origin, ancestry, sex, sexuality, gender, or
187 age.
188 (2) If an [approved] adultprogram provider determines that a student would be better
189 served by participating in a different program, the approved program provider may refer the
190 student to the state's adult basic education services.
191 [12. (1) There is hereby created in the state treasury the "Workforce Diploma
192 Program Fund", which shall consist of any grants, gifts, donations, bequests, or moneys
193 appropriated under this section. The state treasurer shall be custodian of the fund. In
194 accordance with sections 30.170 and 30.180, the state treasurer may approve disbursements.
195 The fund shall be a dedicated fund and, upon appropriation, moneys in the fund shall be used
196 solely as provided in this section.
197 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of section 33.080 to the contrary, any moneys
198 remaining in the fund at the end of the biennium shall not revert to the credit of the general
199 revenue fund.
200 (3) The state treasurer shall invest moneys in the fund in the same manner as other
201 funds are invested. Any interest and moneys earned on such investments shall be credited to
202 the fund.

